-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Brocal, IRL, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-04-12T21:11:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/peru-stocks-buenaventura-maple-southern-copper-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the close.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for the first time this week,
gaining 0.9 percent to 23,471.36. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD) 
climbed 1.3 percent to 2,996.23.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest copper
producer, jumped 5.5 percent to $31.65 after copper advanced the
most in a week in  New York , said Javier Frisancho, a trader at
Lima-based brokerage Kallpa Securities SAB.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner,
gained 3.4 percent to $4.50 after gold climbed to a one-week
high in New York.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, rose 2.4 percent to $42.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. gold producer with a mine
in Peru, gained 1.9 percent to $1.06.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (SMBC)  (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and
copper producer, rose 2 percent to 52 soles after zinc climbed
for a second day in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
